EXAMPLES:	Some examples are already provided in the following language:
			- english,
			- french,
			- dutch,
			- polish.

DESIGN FILE:	eng_text.dgn
		eng_text.dgn


design your text macro in these file and store them as symbol macro
in the corresponding :"VLtext_language" macro library.

template name	: cs
foot_name	: symbol   only one foot

The symbol is a text or a linestring depending on the macro.

To help to create linestring from a text , use the 
"convert text to polygon" command . MAKE SURE that the created
linestring is continous to provide 1 single element to the
marking machine.
Respect the number of characters.


macros in the VLtext macro library are hard-coded
your user-defined macros MUST respect the following names:

TOPsymbol	top direction
BOTsymbol	bottom direction
PRTsymbol	port side
STBsymbol	starboard
FWDsymbol	forepeak
AFTsymbol	afterpeak

DIRsymbol	arrow indicator for stiffener-template

FRTletter	fore peak direction
CTRletter	central axis direction
DWNletter	bottom direction

Macro-libraries: VLtext_eng
	         VLtext_fra
		 VLtext_dut
		 VLtext_pol
